A judge in upstate New York was choked and slammed in the head with a toilet tank lid as he locked up court after an arraignment, according to authorities.

Waterloo acting Judge Roger Barto was attacked from behind Saturday night with a toilet tank lid that had been placed in a nearby garbage container during building renovations, police said.

Officers found Barto lying near the front door of the courtroom entrance. He was taken to Strong Memorial Hospital in Rochester, where he's listed in serious condition.

